<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,355,452]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis box="[151,273,355,380]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,355,380]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Scape, pedicel, legs and abdomen reddish-brown; thorax dark brown to black, opaque, densely grey pruinescent; scutum with four matte-black stripes in anterior view; tiny proepisternal setae; wing elongate, light brown; halter and both thoracic spiracles yellow; sternite 8 sclerotized.
</paragraph>
